article.description: Charde Houston had 20 points and four blocked shots and Ann Strother added 16 points to lead No. 11 Connecticut to an 85-49 win over Syracuse on Saturday.
article.headline: Huskies hand Orange sixth straight loss
article.linkText: No. 11 UConn tramples Syracuse with ease
article.story:
HARTFORD, Conn. (AP) -- Charde Houston had 20 points and four
blocked shots and Ann Strother added 16 points to lead No. 11
Connecticut to an 85-49 win over Syracuse on Saturday.

UConn (18-6, 11-2 Big East) handed the Orange (11-14, 3-11)
their sixth straight loss and made it look easy.

The Huskies put the game away early with a solid first half,
hitting six of their first eight shots for a 15-2 lead. Strother's
3-pointer capped the run and provided a comfortable cushion for the
rest of the game. It was her first of three 3-pointers in the half.

UConn had been averaging 17 turnovers a game, but played through
the first 10 minutes without one and committed just two fouls in
the half.

The Huskies led by as many as 20 in the half. The Orange weren't
able to put consecutive buckets together until the final six
minutes of the period and trailed 43-26 at the break.

Ball-handling got a little sloppier in the second half for the
Huskies, who committed 10 turnovers in the first 12 minutes. But
the cold-shooting Orange couldn't capitalize and didn't score a
point off a UConn miscue all game. Syracuse shot 27 percent
(9-of-35) for the final 20 minutes.

UConn made the most of Syracuse's mistakes, converting 16
turnovers into 28 points. Nicole Wolff had five of UConn's 10
steals and finished with a career-high eight assists.

Rochelle Coleman led the Orange with 19 points, hitting 5-of-9
from 3-point range. Teammate Mary Jo Riley added 10.

UConn junior Barbara Turner recorded her second double-double of
the season with 10 points and 11 rebounds.

The Huskies dominated inside, outrebounding the Orange 52-32 and
outscoring them 40-12 in the paint.
